inlineContent.text: A pointer to an uninitialized DNSServiceRef. If the call succeeds then it initializes the DNSServiceRef, returns
, and the resolve operation will run indefinitely until the client terminates it by passing this DNSServiceRef to
Specifying kDNSServiceFlagsForceMulticast will cause query to be performed with a link-local mDNS query, even if the name is an apparently non-local name (i.e. a name not ending in “.local.”)
The interface on which to resolve the service. If this resolve call is as a result of a currently active

operation, then the interfaceIndex should be the index reported in the DNSServiceBrowseReply callback. If this resolve call is using information previously saved (e.g. in a preference file) for later use, then use interfaceIndex 0, because the desired service may now be reachable via a different physical interface. See “Constants for specifying an interface index” for more details.
The name of the service instance to be resolved, as reported to the
callback.
The type of the service instance to be resolved, as reported to the
callback.
The domain of the service instance to be resolved, as reported to the
callback.
The function to be called when a result is found, or if the call asynchronously fails.
An application context pointer which is passed to the callback function (may be NULL).
Returns

on success (any subsequent, asynchronous errors are delivered to the callback), otherwise returns an error code indicating the error that occurred (the callback is never invoked and the DNSServiceRef is not initialized).

abstract.text: Discover, publish, and resolve network services on a local area or wide area network.
Callback for handling the results of previous calls to DNSServiceBrowse.
Terminates a connection with the daemon and frees memory associated with the DNSServiceRef.
A pointer for accessing data of a specific type.
A pointer for accessing and manipulating data of a specific type.
A raw pointer for accessing and manipulating untyped data.
